=== 軟子音 ===
子音 '''ľ'''、 '''ń'''、 '''ŕ'''、 '''ť'''、 '''ď'''、 '''ś''' 和 '''ź''' 是對應著'''l'''、 '''n'''、 '''r'''、 '''t'''、 '''d'''、 '''s''' 和 '''z'''的[[輔音弱化|軟子音]]。

The latter may also be pronounced like their softened/palatalized equivalents before '''i''', '''ě''', '''ę''' and possibly before '''e'''. This pronunciation is not mandatory, though: they may as well be written and pronounced hard.

Soft consonants are normally represented by an [[acute_accent|acute]] or a [[haček|haček]], but other ways of writing are possible as well: '''nj''', '''n’''', etc. To avoid texts from becoming heavy on diacritics, it is recommended that before a vowel, soft consonants are written as a hard consonant followed by a '''j''': nom. ''koń'', gen. ''konja'' (instead of ''końa'').

